optimize (2.0.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Replace the package build pipeline with profile-based rebuilds:
    vendor, native-safe, native-aggressive, adaptive and custom.
  * Preserve Debian/Ubuntu packaging flow by building through sbuild
    with temporary SBUILD_CONFIG files and package-local changelog
    version suffixes.
  * Enable package tests by default and make nocheck an explicit option.
  * Remove persistent ~/.sbuildrc edits, chmod 777 workspaces, forced
    dpkg overwrites and unsafe sudo cleanup paths.
  * Add development bootstrap, shell quality checks, CLI tests and
    version consistency tests for CI/CD.
  * Let kernel builds continue with O2 and localmodconfig when native
    CPU compiler flags cannot be validated.
  * Resolve kernel builds to unsigned buildable kernel source packages
    instead of signed wrapper sources such as linux-signed-amd64.

 -- helton <chileno.brasil@gmail.com>  Tue, 14 Jul 2026 14:45:00 -0300

